description:
More jazz/music interviews and exclusive coverage of the Rochester International Jazz Festival at: http://www.thehaywire.com

Pianist Stan Tracey, "the godfather of British jazz," speaks to TheHaywire's Saby Reyes-Kulkarni the morning after his 6/11/2010 performance at the Rochester International Jazz Festival. He discusses his early career as Ronnie Scott's house pianist, British jazz, taking a late night bus home from the club, family, and playing with is son Clark. (Handheld camerawork of Christine Carder.)
